00:48.323 --> 00:50.723
- You ever been in love?
- Once.

00:51.124 --> 00:52.604
His name was Elijah.

00:53.497 --> 00:55.806
I can't get a job
until I've passed the bar.

00:55.831 --> 00:57.951
Which I will hopefully know about soon.

00:59.591 --> 01:01.951
I didn't pass the bar.

01:05.223 --> 01:07.650
We don't do grassroots activism here.

01:07.675 --> 01:09.683
At Legal Aid, we're focused mostly

01:09.708 --> 01:11.928
on providing direct legal services

01:11.953 --> 01:13.180
to the local community.

01:19.512 --> 01:21.632
You wouldn't believe what
that woman has been through.

01:22.178 --> 01:24.130
This is Callie, your
new research assistant.

01:24.539 --> 01:25.691
Cary, Gwen.

01:25.716 --> 01:27.374
Hi, I'm Cary. So nice to meet you.

01:27.399 --> 01:28.565
Hi. Nice to meet you. Welcome.

01:28.589 --> 01:29.872
They're our paralegals.

01:29.897 --> 01:32.098
You'll be working for them
and all the lawyers here.

01:32.123 --> 01:34.349
Will you show Callie around,
give her the lay of the land?

01:34.373 --> 01:35.405
Of course.

01:35.430 --> 01:38.271
You are gorgeous.

01:38.435 --> 01:39.892
Is it okay to say that?

01:40.016 --> 01:41.682
Cary's new. Don't worry.

01:41.707 --> 01:44.258
The only person he wants
to harass around here is...

01:44.283 --> 01:45.382
Right behind you.

01:45.407 --> 01:46.473
Marcus.

01:46.498 --> 01:48.307
- Hey.
- This is Callie.

01:48.332 --> 01:49.732
She's our new research assistant.

01:49.757 --> 01:50.757
Oh, good.

01:51.612 --> 01:53.932
Can you check the LARSO
on this three-day notice?

01:58.284 --> 01:59.984
Uh, this is defective.

02:00.009 --> 02:02.245
