08:10.193 --> 08:11.433
Miss me?

08:12.255 --> 08:13.555
What's his story?

08:14.371 --> 08:15.640
- Oh, Dennis?
- Yeah.

08:15.664 --> 08:18.182
- He lives at the Coterie.
- Hm. What does he do?

08:18.207 --> 08:19.923
Well, you're looking at it.

08:19.948 --> 08:21.397
He must have a job.

08:21.422 --> 08:22.662
Not that I know of.

08:23.247 --> 08:25.214
But he just moved in,
so I barely know him.

08:25.239 --> 08:26.731
Well, maybe you should get to know him.

08:26.755 --> 08:28.321
He's very attractive.

08:28.346 --> 08:30.038
Yeah, no thanks.

08:30.063 --> 08:31.254
That guy's a loser.

08:31.279 --> 08:32.895
Every man's a loser

08:32.921 --> 08:34.798
until he finds the right woman.

08:34.823 --> 08:36.273
Oh, thank you.

08:36.298 --> 08:37.655
Hey, can you send Dennis

08:37.681 --> 08:39.100
a refill of whatever he's drinking?

08:39.125 --> 08:40.957
- And say it's from Davia.
- Mom, no.

08:40.982 --> 08:43.203
Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes. Do it,
do it, do it, do it, do it. Yeah.

08:43.227 --> 08:45.207
Okay, what about his date?

08:45.643 --> 08:47.203
Well, she can get her own drink.

08:59.253 --> 09:00.253
Hmm.

09:07.842 --> 09:08.842
Hey, guys.

09:11.495 --> 09:13.035
Are you and Raj dating?

09:18.741 --> 09:21.261
Is that why you chose Raj to be
on your team instead of a woman?

09:21.286 --> 09:23.778
No. No, I-I chose Raj

09:23.803 --> 09:25.395
because he's an excellent engineer.

09:25.420 --> 09:28.165
People might think they got
passed over because you're dating.

09:28.190 --> 09:30.165
Like me, for instance.

09:30.530 --> 09:33.149
You're the reason that Evan fired Josh.

09:33.174 --> 09:35.700
If any of the guys find out
that you're dating someone

09:35.725 --> 09:37.503
on your team, they're
gonna rip you apart.

09:37.528 --> 09:40.229
All of us. It could undermine
everything we're working for.

09:40.254 --> 09:41.500
As head of the grievance committee,

09:41.524 --> 09:42.607
you either need to break up with Raj

09:42.631 --> 09:44.271
or take him off your team.

09:49.210 --> 09:50.610
I think they're right.

09:57.705 --> 09:59.465
- There you go.
- Thank you.

10:00.825 --> 10:02.345
- Hey, man.
- Hey, man.

10:02.369 --> 10:04.234
I heard you took that 5G workshop.

10:04.235 --> 10:06.397
You wanna grab drinks later so
I can pick your brain about it?

10:06.421 --> 10:07.741
Sure, man.

10:16.438 --> 10:17.678
Hey, man.

10:20.950 --> 10:21.950
Hey.

10:23.311 --> 10:25.387
Uh, can I get a double chai latte?

10:25.412 --> 10:26.652
Coming right up.

10:26.677 --> 10:29.017
Very pleased with the
way the app is going.

10:30.813 --> 10:31.813
Yeah.

10:38.083 --> 10:39.723
Would you mind if we spoke in private?

10:45.671 --> 10:47.065
I need a declaration

10:47.090 --> 10:49.094
to complete this petition for dismissal.

10:49.119 --> 10:50.672
- Good morning.
- I said, "Good morning".

10:50.696 --> 10:52.730
No, you didn't. Good morning.

10:52.755 --> 10:54.638
Would you mind cite-checking
this motion for me?

10:54.663 --> 10:55.663
Sure.

10:57.329 --> 10:59.409
- My declaration?
- Yeah, I'll do it.

11:04.129 --> 11:05.129
What's this?

11:05.531 --> 11:07.971
A vanilla latte. For you.

11:08.351 --> 11:10.151
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

11:10.316 --> 11:12.336
I just need that declaration.

11:14.918 --> 11:17.398
He's not in yet. Everything okay?

11:17.876 --> 11:18.876
Yeah.

11:20.522 --> 11:23.656
Callie, this is my father, Joseph.

11:24.876 --> 11:26.036
He's being evicted.

11:27.356 --> 11:28.596
I think because of us.

11:30.405 --> 11:33.514
They can't evict you for making
a complaint about maintenance.

11:35.163 --> 11:36.463
I'm behind on my rent.

11:37.471 --> 11:39.770
I ran into some medical
bills a few months ago.

11:39.795 --> 11:41.621
The landlord was letting me stay

11:41.623 --> 11:43.676
in exchange for doing
odd jobs around the place.

11:43.700 --> 11:45.669
But then he accused me of snitching

11:45.694 --> 11:47.244
about the broken elevator

11:47.269 --> 11:48.979
and gave me 24 hours to get out.

11:49.004 --> 11:50.844
I'm so sorry, Joseph.

11:51.948 --> 11:55.028
But don't worry. I'll get someone
from my office to fix this.

11:56.680 --> 11:58.272
Good morning, Marcus.

11:58.297 --> 11:59.817
- Hey, Marcus.
- Morning.

12:00.117 --> 12:01.411
Uh, Marcus, can I talk to you?

12:01.436 --> 12:03.256
Yes. Make it quick. I have a client.

12:03.281 --> 12:06.833
I wanted to talk to you
about that demand letter.

12:06.858 --> 12:08.108
What demand letter is that?

12:08.133 --> 12:09.750
Uh, the one you told
me to serve on the...

12:09.771 --> 12:12.171
Towers on Western
single residency hotel.

12:12.196 --> 12:14.656
Elevator's been out for weeks,
and management keeps saying

12:14.681 --> 12:16.567
they're gonna fix it and they don't.

12:16.592 --> 12:18.112
I was wondering what can be done.

12:18.137 --> 12:19.735
Well, we would serve a demand letter

12:19.760 --> 12:22.205
saying that they have 48
hours to address the problem.

12:22.230 --> 12:23.647
Otherwise, they're in breach,

12:23.672 --> 12:25.832
and they could lose
their license to operate.

12:28.068 --> 12:29.068
Okay.

12:30.039 --> 12:31.279
I know what to do.

12:33.532 --> 12:35.532
What I don't understand is

12:35.557 --> 12:37.298
how the manager knew Joseph had anything

12:37.323 --> 12:39.031
to do with the demand letter?

12:39.056 --> 12:40.376
I didn't put his name on it.

12:42.086 --> 12:43.286
I think that's on me.

12:45.906 --> 12:47.406
Selina, you okay?

12:48.927 --> 12:50.562
The elevator's still broken.

12:50.587 --> 12:52.587
Yeah, I can't do my shopping.

12:57.814 --> 13:00.489
No man has carried me like this

13:00.514 --> 13:03.556
since my husband carried
me across the threshold.

13:05.503 --> 13:07.503
God rest his rotten heart.

13:07.528 --> 13:08.688
Oh.

13:12.864 --> 13:13.864
Okay.

13:15.814 --> 13:17.574
Alright. I'll go get
your wheelchair, huh?

13:17.599 --> 13:18.701
Just hang tight.

13:18.726 --> 13:20.476
What else could I do?

13:21.599 --> 13:22.839
Here you go.

13:24.215 --> 13:25.889
So, how long has the elevator been out?

13:25.922 --> 13:27.047
A while.

13:27.072 --> 13:29.056
They keep saying they're
gonna fix it, but...

13:29.081 --> 13:30.634
in the meantime, people like Selina

13:30.659 --> 13:31.779
are trapped on their floors.

13:32.379 --> 13:34.619
That's not right. There's
gotta be something they can do.

13:34.901 --> 13:35.958
Well, we'll manage.

13:35.983 --> 13:37.663
Well...

13:38.277 --> 13:39.877
I'd like to see you again sometime.

13:40.218 --> 13:41.218
If it suits you.

13:42.761 --> 13:44.721
- Yeah. I'd, I'd like that, too.
- Yeah.

14:00.439 --> 14:02.448
I'm gonna die soon.

14:03.857 --> 14:06.316
Oh, no. Don't you bet on it, Selina.

14:06.341 --> 14:08.372
You're gonna outlive us all.

14:17.216 --> 14:18.216
Excuse me.

14:19.152 --> 14:21.272
Can I ask when you plan
on fixing the elevator?

14:21.297 --> 14:23.016
Who the hell are you?
You don't live here.

14:23.466 --> 14:24.701
My father does.

14:24.896 --> 14:26.513
And the tenants who can't use the stairs

14:26.538 --> 14:27.624
are stuck on their floors.

14:27.821 --> 14:29.061
It's none of your business.

14:30.518 --> 14:32.758
Then I'll take it to someone
whose business it is.

14:33.860 --> 14:35.937
You served a demand letter?

14:35.962 --> 14:37.771
That's what you said we do...

14:37.796 --> 14:40.036
We, as in one of the licensed lawyers.

14:42.480 --> 14:43.880
I guess I misunderstood.

14:44.708 --> 14:45.948
Is that it?

14:46.589 --> 14:48.213
No. Um,

14:48.238 --> 14:49.814
there's a problem.

14:49.839 --> 14:53.031
The tenant on whose
behalf I served the letter

14:53.060 --> 14:54.940
is being evicted in retaliation.

14:55.522 --> 14:56.904
They can't do that.

14:56.929 --> 14:58.089
Well, he's behind on rent.

14:58.906 --> 15:01.541
And he's the father of a friend of mine,

15:01.566 --> 15:04.826
so I feel like this is sort of my fault.

15:04.851 --> 15:06.410
Yeah. Ya think?

15:07.565 --> 15:08.865
Is there something we...

15:09.582 --> 15:11.307
you can do to help him?

15:11.332 --> 15:14.349
Maybe. But I can't do anything
without looping in Teresa.

15:15.221 --> 15:18.241
And if I do that, your first
week here might be your last.

15:25.548 --> 15:27.415
So, I made a mistake.

15:32.889 --> 15:35.015
There was a... glitch

15:35.040 --> 15:36.880
- in the beta test...
- Raj told me.

15:39.137 --> 15:40.782
What exactly did he tell you?

15:40.807 --> 15:43.247
That it doubled the amount of
donations, and it was his fault.

15:44.735 --> 15:46.186
No, i-it was my fault.

15:46.211 --> 15:47.581
I-it was in the original code.

15:47.606 --> 15:49.275
He was just trying to fix it on the fly.

15:49.300 --> 15:51.766
He asked me to garnish his
wages to make up the extra money.

15:51.791 --> 15:53.318
That's what I was gonna ask you to do,

15:53.343 --> 15:54.951
t-to my wages.

15:54.976 --> 15:57.133
I'm the team leader.
It's my responsibility.

15:58.774 --> 15:59.974
I'm the company leader.

